<Base title="PHLIPPED · n0t.space" description="Physical Layered Intrusion Prevention, Protection & Evaluation Defense">
  <h1>PHLIPPED</h1>
  <p><strong>Physical Layered Intrusion Prevention, Protection &amp; Evaluation Defense.</strong></p>
  <p>A defensive framework for the Flipper Zero era of physical attacks. Purple-team oriented: for every catalogued attack, three layers (prevent, detect, respond) mapped to MITRE ATT&amp;CK, MITRE D3FEND, NIST CSF 2.0, ISO 27001 Annex A, and NIS2.</p>

  <h2>Components</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Threat Catalog</strong> — hierarchical taxonomy of physical electronic attacks.</li>
    <li><strong>Assessment Methodology</strong> — auditable checklist + Physical Security Posture Score (PSPS).</li>
    <li><strong>Detection Layer</strong> — Wazuh + Sigma rules per threat.</li>
    <li><strong>Hardening Playbook</strong> — prevent/detect/respond per threat, mapped to € and effort.</li>
    <li><strong>Reference implementation</strong> — <code>phlipped-assess</code> CLI, <code>phlipped-lab</code> docker-compose.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Links</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Docs: <a href="https://docs.n0t.space">docs.n0t.space</a></li>
    <li>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/phlipped-fw">github.com/phlipped-fw</a></li>
    <li>Repos: <code>phlipped-catalog</code>, <code>phlipped-rules</code>, <code>phlipped-assess</code>, <code>phlipped-lab</code></li>
  </ul>

  <p style="margin-top:2rem; color:#888;"><em>Attackers have Flipper Zero. Defenders have PHLIPPED.</em></p>
</Base>
